Note:
compiler/backend/bytecode_gen/generator.runa
Main Bytecode Generation Engine

This module provides comprehensive bytecode generation functionality including:
- MIR to bytecode translation and encoding
- Bytecode instruction selection and optimization
- Register allocation and stack frame management
- Control flow bytecode generation
- Function call and return bytecode generation
- Exception handling bytecode generation
- Memory management bytecode integration
- AOTT-ready bytecode generation with metadata
- Profiling hook insertion for runtime optimization
- Deoptimization metadata embedding
- Speculation point marking and guard insertion
- Bytecode optimization and peephole improvements
- Cross-platform bytecode generation
- Integration with runtime execution tiers
:End Note

Import "dev/debug/errors/core" as Errors

Note: =====================================================================
Note: BYTECODE GENERATION DATA STRUCTURES
Note: =====================================================================

Type called "BytecodeInstruction":
    opcode as String
    operands as List[String]
    instruction_offset as Integer
    source_location as String
    optimization_tier as Integer
    profiling_enabled as Boolean
    deopt_info as String
    speculation_guard as String

Type called "BytecodeFunction":
    function_name as String
    instruction_sequence as List[BytecodeInstruction]
    local_variable_count as Integer
    parameter_count as Integer
    stack_size as Integer
    exception_handlers as List[String]
    profiling_metadata as Dictionary[String, String]
    deopt_metadata as Dictionary[String, String]

Type called "BytecodeModule":
    module_name as String
    functions as List[BytecodeFunction]
    constant_pool as List[String]
    type_information as Dictionary[String, String]
    import_table as List[String]
    export_table as List[String]
    aott_metadata as Dictionary[String, String]

